.SH NAME
WebGL2RenderingContext.getUniformBlockIndex \- WebGL2RenderingContext:
getUniformBlockIndex() method
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]WebGL2RenderingContext.getUniformBlockIndex()\f[B]\f[R]
method of the WebGL 2 API retrieves the index of a uniform block within
a \f[CR]WebGLProgram\f[R].
.SH SYNTAX
.IP
.EX
getUniformBlockIndex(program, uniformBlockName)
.EE
.SS Parameters
.TP
\f[B]program\f[R]
A \f[CR]WebGLProgram\f[R] containing the uniform block.
.TP
\f[B]uniformName\f[R]
A string specifying the name of the uniform block to whose index to
retrieve.
.SS Return value
A \f[CR]GLuint\f[R] indicating the uniform block index.
.SH EXAMPLES
.IP
.EX
\f[I]// Assuming a shader with the following declaration:\f[R]
\f[I]// uniform UBOData {\f[R]
\f[I]//   mat4 foo;\f[R]
\f[I]// } instanceName;\f[R]

\f[I]// use the block name, not the instance name:\f[R]
\f[B]const\f[R] blockIndex = gl.getUniformBlockIndex(program, \[dq]UBOData\[dq]);
.EE
